## Summary

DC-2 is a beginner-friendly WordPress machine. The attack chain involves generating a custom CeWL wordlist to brute force WordPress credentials, SSH access on a non-standard port, escaping a restricted shell (rbash) via vi, lateral movement between users, and privilege escalation via a sudo git misconfiguration.

