## Enumeration

### Step 1 — Hosts File Setup

Initial nmap showed the site redirecting to `http://dc-2`. Added the hostname to `/etc/hosts`:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/hosts
# Add: 192.168.56.107  dc-2
```

### Step 2 — Port Scanning

Standard scan only found port 80. A full port scan revealed SSH on a non-standard port:

```bash
nmap -sC -sV 192.168.56.107        # initial scan
nmap -sV -p- 192.168.56.107        # full port scan
```

**Results:**

```
PORT     STATE SERVICE VERSION
80/tcp   open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.10 (Debian)
7744/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 6.7p1 Debian
```

> **Lesson:** Always run a full `-p-` scan if the initial scan seems incomplete.

### Step 3 — WordPress Enumeration

The site was a WordPress 4.7.10 installation. Flag 1 was visible on the `/flag` page after loading the site.

**Enumerate users with WPScan:**

```bash
wpscan --url http://dc-2 --enumerate u
```

**Found 3 users:**
- `admin`
- `jerry`
- `tom`

