## Key Takeaways

- Always run a **full port scan** (`-p-`) — non-standard ports are common in CTFs
- **CeWL** generates target-specific wordlists that generic lists miss
- **rbash** can be escaped via editors like vi/vim that can spawn shells
- Always run **`sudo -l`** after getting a shell — sudo misconfigurations are a very common privesc vector
- Check [GTFOBins](https://gtfobins.github.io) for any binary you can run with sudo

